quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  3,16,"who say, “Our Lord, we have indeed attained faith, so forgive us our misdeeds and guard us from the punishment of the Fire.”"
  3,17,"The patient and the truthful and the devout and the spenders<i class=""s"">(in the way of God) </i>and the seekers of forgiveness before dawn."
  3,18,"Allah has borne witness that indeed, there is no god but He, as have the angels and those endowed with knowledge—upholding justice. There is no god but He, the Almighty, the All-Wise."
  3,19,"<span class=""h"">Indeed<sup foot_note=""79758"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>, religion with Allah is Islam. Yet those who were brought the Scripture did not differ with each other except after knowledge had come to them, thereby oppressing one another. So whoever denies the signs of Allah—then Allah is indeed Swift in reckoning."
  3,20,"So if they debate with you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, then say, “I have submitted my countenance to Allah, and<i class=""s"">(so have) </i>those who have followed me.” And say to those who were brought the Scripture and to the gentiles{1}, “Have you submitted?” Thus, if they have submitted, then they have been guided. But if they turn away, then your<i class=""s"">(only) </i>duty is proclamation, for Allah is All-Seeing of the servants.",footnotes:1:Literally ‘the unlettered’.
  3,21,"Indeed, those who deny Allah’s signs{1}and unjustifiably kill the prophets and <span class=""h"">kill<sup foot_note=""79761"" class=""qiraat"">2</sup> </span>those of mankind who command to justice—give them glad tidings{3}of a painful punishment.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used isayat(singularayah). Ayahmeans ‘sign’ or ‘proof’. It is also used to denote the unit of text in the Qur’an,like ‘verse’ in poetry or ‘sentence’ in prose.Each such unit isconsidered a ‘sign’from God.|3:This is said in sarcasm.
  3,22,"Those are the ones whose deeds were nullified in the Earlier<i class=""s"">(Life) </i>and the Hereafter, for they have no helpers."
